{"award_age":63.0,"bio_image":"full\/aab99e57a5fd8315b71ec421e63343d3528e23d5.jpg","category":"Economics","country":"United States","date_of_birth":"1918-03-05T00:00:00.000Z","date_of_death":"2002-03-11T00:00:00.000Z","gender":"male","image_urls":["http:\/\/upload.wikimedia.org\/wikipedia\/commons\/thumb\/1\/11\/James_Tobin.png\/220px-James_Tobin.png"],"link":"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/James_Tobin","mini_bio":"<p><b>James Tobin<\/b> (March 5, 1918 \u2013 March 11, 2002) was an <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/United_States\" title=\"United States\">American<\/a> <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Economist\" title=\"Economist\">economist<\/a> who, in his lifetime, served on the <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Council_of_Economic_Advisors\" title=\"Council of Economic Advisors\" class=\"mw-redirect\">Council of Economic Advisors<\/a> and the <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Board_of_Governors\" title=\"Board of Governors\" class=\"mw-redirect\">Board of Governors<\/a> of the <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Federal_Reserve_System\" title=\"Federal Reserve System\">Federal Reserve System<\/a>, and taught at <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Harvard\" title=\"Harvard\" class=\"mw-redirect\">Harvard<\/a> and <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Yale\" title=\"Yale\" class=\"mw-redirect\">Yale<\/a> Universities. He developed the ideas of <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Keynesian_economics\" title=\"Keynesian economics\">Keynesian economics<\/a>, and advocated <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Government_intervention\" title=\"Government intervention\" class=\"mw-redirect\">government intervention<\/a> to stabilize output and avoid <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Recession\" title=\"Recession\">recessions<\/a>. His academic work included pioneering contributions to the study of <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Investment_(macroeconomics)\" title=\"Investment (macroeconomics)\">investment<\/a>, monetary and <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Fiscal_policy\" title=\"Fiscal policy\">fiscal policy<\/a> and financial markets. He also proposed an <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Econometric_model\" title=\"Econometric model\">econometric model<\/a> for censored <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Endogenous\" title=\"Endogenous\" class=\"mw-redirect\">endogenous<\/a> variables, the well-known \"<a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Tobit_model\" title=\"Tobit model\">Tobit model<\/a>\". Tobin received the <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Nobel_Memorial_Prize_in_Economic_Sciences\" title=\"Nobel Memorial Prize in Economic Sciences\">Nobel Memorial Prize in Economic Sciences<\/a> in 1981.<\/p><p>Outside of academia, Tobin was widely known for his suggestion of a <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Tax\" title=\"Tax\">tax<\/a> on <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Foreign_exchange_market\" title=\"Foreign exchange market\">foreign exchange<\/a> transactions, now known as the \"<a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Tobin_tax\" title=\"Tobin tax\">Tobin tax<\/a>\". This was designed to reduce <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Speculation\" title=\"Speculation\">speculation<\/a> in the international <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Currency_market\" title=\"Currency market\" class=\"mw-redirect\">currency markets<\/a>, which he saw as dangerous and unproductive.<\/p>","name":"James Tobin","place_of_birth":"Champaign, Illinois ,  USA","place_of_death":"New Haven, Connecticut , USA","text":"James Tobin , Economics, 1981","year":1981.0}